0":"1390","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Woodbridge, Suffolk, England":"Woodbridge, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":67,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born in 1388, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 son with Thomas De Henrico Packard. She died in 1467, in Woodbridge, Suffolk, England, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1388–1467":"1388–1467","1390–1457":"1390–1457","1410–1471":"1410–1471","1457":"1457","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1410":"1410","1471":"1471","about 1410":"umbes 1410","1390":"1390","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Woodbridge, Suffolk, England":"Woodbridge, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1388–1467":"1388–1467","1390–1457":"1390–1457","1410–1471":"1410–1471","1457":"1457","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1410":"1410","1471":"1471","about 1410":"noin 1410","1390":"1390","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Woodbridge, Suffolk, England":"Woodbridge, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1388–1467":"1388–1467","1390–1457":"1390–1457","1410–1471":"1410–1471","1457":"1457","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1410":"1410","1471":"1471","about 1410":"environ 1410","1390":"1390","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Angleterre","Woodbridge, Suffolk, England":"Woodbridge, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Matilda est née en 1388, à Ipswich, Suffolk, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Thomas De Henrico Packard. Elle est décédée en 1467, à Woodbridge, Suffolk, Angleterre, à l’âge de 79 ans."},"de":{"1388–1467":"1388–1467","1390–1457":"1390–1457","1410–1471":"1410–1471","1457":"1457","1467":"1467","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1410":"1410","1471":"1471","about 1410":"um 1410","1390":"1390","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, England","Woodbridge, Suffolk, England":"Woodbridge, Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Matilda wurde 1388 in Ipswich, Suffolk, England geboren. Sie hatte mit Thomas De Henrico Packard mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1467 im